<br>
The type of loot distribution will be posted with the raid information on the guild message board.<br>
<br>
·      The raid leader will determine how the loot will be distributed. The two main  ways to do this as covered below:<br>
<br>
           &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NBG</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> – Need Before Greed – This method takes in consideration the ability of a character to use the item including level considerations. It is not useful to give a 50 AC BP with STR and STA stats to a wizzy. This may upset the greedy characters but is very beneficial to the guild as a whole. Remember when you need that dragon epic mob the strength of the characters in the guild are what will be the determining factor on whether or not you will be successful.<br>
<br>
          &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>GREED</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> – everyone rolls on everything. At lower levels this may be the norm but does nothing to strengthen a guild’s power and ability.<br>
<br>
·      The Raid Leader will do the rolling or designate the ML’s to do so. He/she will call for those who are eligible to roll on an item, assign them a number and cast the roll. This is much less confusing and faster.<br>
<br>
·      In a NBG loot system if the item that you are rolling on IS NOT an upgrade for you pass on the roll. This will help to strengthen our classes faster. If it is not an upgrade for any of that class then the item can be greed rolled by all.<br>
<br>
·       No items will be rolled on for your alts. Only the participating characters are eligible. For example a rouge item drops and none are present then the item will be greed rolled after the raid. <br>
<br>
·      Keep in mind that some items may be defaulted to a particular character or class. This information will be posted on the guild board. For example epic drops, class only quest items, etc. <br>
<br>
·      The Raid Leader will designate the person or persons that will be the ML’s (Master Looters). This ensures integrity in loot distribution and eliminates finger pointing and hard feelings. <br>
<br>
·      DO NOT loot anything unless you are the ML or the Raid Leader instructs you to do so. Ninja Looting will not be tolerated and may result in your being asked to leave the current raid or even to be suspended from the next event.<br>
<br>
·      All loot will be rolled on AFTER the raid is complete. If for some reason you have to leave the RL may roll for you ONLY choosing from the loot that was obtained prior to your absence. <br>
<br>
·      No Drop loot will be rolled on immediately after the fighting is over and things are safe.<br>
<br>
·      Once a person has rolled and won an item they will not roll again until everyone has won something.<br>
<br>
·      Roll only on things that are useful to your class. (refer to the reason for NBG looting)<br>
<br>
·      The common (junk) loot that will be sold at a vendor, and money, will go to the guild bank to pay for spells, reagents (ie, peridots, pearls, etc.).<br>
<br>
Remember do not expect loot. You may get something but then again you may not. Just be happy that the goal is obtained (as in an epic raid) and remember even if you didn’t get anything people will remember your assistance in the future when it comes to your epic raids and will return the favor.<br>
